BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 175.44 740 Td (Chapter 2: Choosing Yarn and Hooks) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 70 725 m 542 725 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 700 Td (Yarn comes in different weights from lace \(very thin\) to jumbo \(very thick\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 676 Td (The yarn label tells you everything: weight, hook size, fiber content, and yardage.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 652 Td (Weight 4 \(worsted/medium\) is the standard learning weight for all beginners.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 628 Td (Popular beginner yarn brands include Red Heart Super Saver and Caron Simply Soft.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 604 Td (Hooks are sized by millimeters and also have letter designations.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 580 Td (The yarn label recommends which hook size to use for best results.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 556 Td (Larger hooks create looser, more open fabric. Smaller hooks create tighter fabric.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 532 Td (Ergonomic hooks with cushioned handles reduce hand fatigue during long sessions.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 508 Td (As you advance, you will explore cotton yarn, bamboo, wool, and specialty fibers.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 484 Td (Buy one skein of light-colored worsted yarn and the matching hook to start.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 460 Td (Do not invest in a large yarn collection until you know what you enjoy making.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 436 Td (The relationship between yarn weight and hook size is the most important concept.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 303.6 40 Td (2) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
