BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 210.0 740 Td (Chapter 6: Single Crochet) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 70 725 m 542 725 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 700 Td (Single crochet is the most basic and most used stitch in all of crochet.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 676 Td (Start with a foundation chain of fifteen stitches for practice.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 652 Td (Skip the first chain from the hook and insert your hook into the second chain.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 628 Td (Yarn over and pull through the chain only. You now have two loops on your hook.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 604 Td (Yarn over again and pull through both loops on the hook. One single crochet complete.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 580 Td (Insert your hook into the next chain and repeat the same two steps.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 556 Td (Continue across the entire chain making one single crochet in each stitch.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 532 Td (At the end of the row, chain one and turn your work to the other side.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 508 Td (For the next row, insert your hook under both loops of each stitch below.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 484 Td (Single crochet creates a dense, tight fabric perfect for washcloths and amigurumi.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 460 Td (Count your stitches at the end of each row. You should have the same number.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 436 Td (Practice rows of single crochet until you can maintain consistent stitch count.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 303.6 40 Td (6) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
