stream
BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 210.0 740 Td (Chapter 7: Double Crochet) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 70 725 m 542 725 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 700 Td (Double crochet is taller than single crochet and works up faster.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 676 Td (Start with a foundation chain. Yarn over before inserting into the stitch.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 652 Td (Insert your hook into the fourth chain from the hook for the first double crochet.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 628 Td (Yarn over and pull through the chain. You now have three loops on your hook.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 604 Td (Yarn over and pull through the first two loops. Two loops remain on the hook.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 580 Td (Yarn over and pull through the last two loops. One double crochet is complete.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 556 Td (The yarn over before inserting is what makes this stitch taller than single crochet.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 532 Td (At the end of a row, chain three and turn. The chain-three counts as a stitch.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 508 Td (Skip the first stitch and double crochet into each stitch across the row.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 484 Td (Double crochet creates an airier fabric great for blankets, scarves, and garments.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 460 Td (This stitch uses more yarn than single crochet because of the extra height.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 436 Td (Once you master double crochet, you can make blankets quickly and beautifully.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 303.6 40 Td (7) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
