stream
BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 175.44 740 Td (Chapter 11: Making a Granny Square) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 70 725 m 542 725 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 700 Td (The granny square is the most iconic crochet motif and a must-learn project.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 676 Td (Start with a magic ring or chain 4 and slip stitch to form a ring.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 652 Td (Round 1: chain 3, make 2 double crochets into the ring, chain 2.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 628 Td (Repeat three more times: 3 double crochets into ring, chain 2. Join with slip stitch.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 604 Td (You now have four groups of three double crochets forming a square shape.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 580 Td (Round 2: slip stitch to the chain-2 corner space.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 556 Td (In each corner space work: 3 DC, chain 2, 3 DC. This creates the corner.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 532 Td (Join at the end of the round with a slip stitch to the top of chain 3.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 508 Td (Each subsequent round adds 3 DC groups in corners and along sides.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 484 Td (Granny squares can be made any size by adding more rounds.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 460 Td (Join multiple granny squares together to make blankets, bags, and cardigans.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 436 Td (This versatile motif teaches you to work in rounds and read pattern structures.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 301.2 40 Td (11) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
34 0 obj
<< /Type /Page /Parent 2 0 R /MediaBox [0 0 612 792] /Contents 35 0 R /Resources << /Font << /F1 3 0 R /F2 4 0 R /F3 5 0 R /F4 6 0 R /F5 7 0 R >> >> >>
endobj
