<< /Length 1494 >>
stream
BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 167.76 740 Td (Chapter 12: Your First Scarf Project) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 70 725 m 542 725 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 700 Td (A scarf is the perfect first project because it only uses rows of one stitch.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 676 Td (Choose a soft medium weight yarn in a color you love for this project.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 652 Td (Chain 25 stitches for a scarf approximately 5 inches wide when finished.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 628 Td (Work in double crochet for a scarf that works up quickly and drapes nicely.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 604 Td (Row 1: double crochet in the fourth chain from hook and each chain across.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 580 Td (Row 2: chain 3, turn. Double crochet in each stitch across. Repeat this row.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 556 Td (Continue until your scarf reaches approximately 60 inches long or desired length.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 532 Td (Count your stitches at the end of every few rows to catch mistakes early.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 508 Td (If you gain or lose stitches, you are likely missing the last stitch or adding extra.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 484 Td (Add fringe by cutting yarn lengths and looping them through the short edges.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 460 Td (Block your finished scarf by wetting it and pinning it flat to dry for even shape.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 436 Td (Congratulations! You have completed your first wearable crochet project.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 301.2 40 Td (12) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
