BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 152.4 740 Td (Chapter 13: Your First Dishcloth Project) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 70 725 m 542 725 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 700 Td (Dishcloths are quick, useful projects that make great gifts and practice pieces.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 676 Td (Use 100 percent cotton yarn which is absorbent and machine washable.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 652 Td (Sugar n Cream or Lily brand cotton yarn is perfect for dishcloths.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 628 Td (Chain 30 stitches for an approximately 8-inch square dishcloth.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 604 Td (Work entirely in single crochet for a dense, scrubby texture ideal for dishes.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 580 Td (Row 1: single crochet in the second chain from hook and each chain across.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 556 Td (Row 2: chain 1, turn. Single crochet in each stitch across. Repeat this row.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 532 Td (Continue for about 30 rows until your piece is roughly square.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 508 Td (Fasten off by cutting the yarn and pulling the tail through the last loop.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 484 Td (Weave in your yarn tails using a yarn needle through nearby stitches.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 460 Td (Try making dishcloths in different colors or add stripes for variety.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 60 436 Td (A dishcloth takes only one to two hours and teaches you consistent tension.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 301.2 40 Td (13) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
